In this article, President Obama discusses his decision to nominate Judge Merrick Garland to the Supreme Court of the United States. He emphasizes the importance of taking this nomination seriously, despite the volatile political climate. The President calls on Republican Senators to give Judge Garland a fair hearing and vote. He highlights Judge Garland's experience, integrity, and dedication to protecting basic rights. President Obama stresses that the Supreme Court should be above politics and urges Senators to fulfill their constitutional obligation. He concludes by expressing his hope for a bipartisan confirmation of Judge Garland, in order to maintain the principles and vision of the country's founders.